To print the title of the song, you need to call the getter method for the title property (usually `getTitle()`) on the object returned by the `peek()` method.

```java
package umg.edu.gt.data_estructure.queue.queueHandler;

import umg.edu.gt.data_structure.queue.manual.QueueLinked;
import umg.edu.gt.model.Song;

public class Main 
{
    public static void main( String[] args )
    {

    	Song song1 = new Song ("Glimpse of us","Joji",30,1);
    	Song song2 = new Song ("Mania Cardiaca","Enjambre",15,2);
    	Song song3 = new Song ("MELT","MASS OF FERMENTING DREGS",20,1);

    	QueueLinked<Song> queue = new QueueLinked<>();
    	queue.enqueue(song1);
    	queue.enqueue(song2);
    	queue.enqueue(song3);

    	// Accessing the title property from the peeked Song object
    	if (queue.peek() != null) {
    	    System.out.println(queue.peek().getTitle());
    	}
    }
}
```

